<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
When a Possessor possesses an Illusionist and attempts to cast spell 'h' - Darkness, the game crashes without saving <p>
<strong><a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a></strong>: This isn't guest's fault at all (and thanks for posting the report, btw!) but something weird's going on with the bugreport numbering system.... 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./NeilStevens">NeilStevens</a></strong>: Well, you and one other person (the one who complained about the docs being terribly out of date,  I think) skipped some numbers.   I wouldn't worry about it.  What matters is that they are unique and mostly sequential.  We have more than enough numbers left to skip a few once in a while, though. 
</p>

    <ul>

 <strong><a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a></strong>: Did I? Ooops! *blush* Which bug report was the infamous complainer, anyway? I can't seem to find it. 
    </ul>


<p>
<strong><a href="./TobiasParker">TobiasParker</a></strong>:I originally posted this...not sure what happened.  Full report(as much as i can remember)<br>
 <br>
 I was an Ent Possessor in a Dark Elven Mage corpse.<br>
 I had The Phial of Galadriel and some created artifact bolts (of Lucil i think) both of which gave light radius.<br>
 
</p>
<p>
I thought it may of had something to do with a permanent light source for obvious reasons.<br>
 I tried this both in Town during day and night and in a dungeon it crashed all times.<br>
 That is all i can remember...character died in Angband...i got a little cocky after i found Medusa's corpse. <br>
 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MassimilianoMarangio">MassimilianoMarangio</a>: Could not reproduce the bug while in a Dark Elven Mage body and Illusionist body wearing the Phial. Will try the normal Possessor way instead of debug commands. See also <a href="./BugReport152">BugReport152</a>. 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./TobiasParker">TobiasParker</a></strong>: Try attempting this when in Gondolin and Mirkwood, those were the 2 locations i was in when it occured. 
</p>
